\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
We develop a political economy model of the housing market in order to estimate
 the impact of NIMBYism.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The model shows that an aging society exacerbates the effects of NIMBYism
 resulting in a 10% increase in the house price to income ratio since 1950.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Baby boomers used outsized voting power to increase their homeownership.
 However, they also decrease homeownership for subsequent generations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Using demographic projections, we forecast the house price to income ratio
 will continue to rise in the 21st century.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
